External module "lib-common/base64"

This module provides an object with functions that encode array of octets (binary data) into base64 strings. Bytes, array of octets, are assumed to be in Uint8Array form, and the same is produced in decoding.

Base64 implemented here uses alphabet, described in https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4648 (RFC 4648), i.e. last to chars are '+' and '/', with '=' used for padding, in a strict correspondence of steps, described in RFC document. Base64 encoder will not tolerate neither non-alphabet characters, nor missing padding characters, if these are required, as per quoted RFC document.

There is an urlSafe object with url safe version of base64.
